olive oil
2 potato
1 carrot
1 parsnip
1 tin sweetcorn
1 packet beef mince
1 sachet Tex-Mex spice blend
1 packet fine breadcrumbs
1 egg
1 packet Smoked Cheddar Cheese
1 packet mayonnaise
1 packet Mild Chipotle Sauce
1 bag parsley

• Preheat oven to 240°C/220°C fan-forced. Cut potato, carrot and parsnip into bite-sized chunks. Drain the sweetcorn.
• Place veggies on a lined oven tray. Drizzle with olive oil, season with salt and toss to coat.
• Roast for 10 minutes.

TIP: If your oven tray is crowded, divide between two trays.

• SPICY! This is a mild spice blend, but use less if you're sensitive to heat! In a medium bowl, combine beef mince, Tex-Mex spice blend, fine breadcrumbs, the egg and a pinch of salt.
• Using damp hands, roll heaped spoonfuls of beef mixture into small meatballs (4-5 per person). Transfer to a plate.

Little cooks: Join the fun by helping combine the ingredients and shaping the mixture into meatballs!

• Place meatballs on the tray with the veggies, then bake until meatballs are golden and cooked through and veggies are tender, 15-20 minutes.
• In last 5 minutes of cook time, remove from oven, sprinkle smoked Cheddar cheese over the veggies and bake until golden and crispy.
• Meanwhile, combine mayonnaise and mild chipotle sauce in a small bowl.

Little cooks: Take charge by combining the sauces!

• Divide Mexican beef meatballs and cheesy roast veggies between plates.
• Drizzle with chipotle mayo and tear over parsley to serve. Enjoy!